l></li><li><a href=\"#\"><strong>Methoden</strong></a><ol><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__defineGetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__defineGetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__defineSetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__defineSetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__lookupGetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__lookupGetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__lookupSetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__lookupSetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/hasOwnProperty\"><code>Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty()</code></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/isPrototypeOf\"><code>Object.prototype.isPrototypeOf()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/propertyIsEnumerable\"><code>Object.prototype.propertyIsEnumerable()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/setPrototypeOf\"><code>Object.setPrototypeOf()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toLocaleString\"><code>Object.prototype.toLocaleString()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toString\"><code>Object.prototype.toString()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/valueOf\"><code>Object.prototype.valueOf()</code></a></li></ol></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div id=\"sect1\"></div>\n\n<p>Die&nbsp;<strong><code>Math.min()</code></strong>&nbsp;Funktion gibt den Wert der kleinsten übergebenen Zahl zurück oder <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/NaN\"><code>NaN</code></a>, wenn ein Parameter keine Zahl ist und auch nicht in eine Zahl konvertiert werden kann.</p>\n\n<div id=\"sect2\"><iframe class=\"interactive\" height=\"490\" src=\"https://interactive-examples.mdn.mozilla.net/pages/js/math-min.html\" title=\"MDN Web Docs Interactive Example\" loading=\"lazy\"></iframe></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<pre class=\"syntaxbox notranslate\"><code>Math.min([<var>value1</var>[, <var>value2</var>[, ...]]])</code></pre>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parameters","title":"Parameter","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n <dt id=\"value1_value2_\"><code>value1, value2, ...</code></dt>\n <dd>Zahlen.</dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"rückgabewert","title":"Rückgabewert","isH3":true,"content":"<p>Die kleinste der übergebenen Zahlen. Wenn nur ein Parameter nicht zu einer Zahl konvertiert werden kann, wird <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/NaN\"><code>NaN</code></a> zurückgegeben.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"description","title":"Beschreibung","isH3":false,"content":"<p>Da&nbsp;<code>min()</code>&nbsp;eine statische Eigenschaft von&nbsp;<code>Math</code> ist, muss immer&nbsp;<code>Math.min()</code> genutzt werden, ohne dass ein&nbsp;<code>Math-</code>Objekt erstellt wird&nbsp;(<code>Math</code>&nbsp;ist kein Konstruktor).</p>\n\n<p>Ohne Übergabeparameter wird&nbsp;<a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Infinity\"><code>Infinity</code></a> zurückgegeben.</p>\n\n<p>Wenn mindestens ein Übergabeparameter nicht in eine Zahl konvertiert werden kann wird <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/NaN\"><code>NaN</code></a> zurückgegeben.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Beispiele","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"example_using_math.min","title":"Einsatz von <code>Math.min()</code>","isH3":true,"content":"<p>Dies findet den kleinsten Wert aus x und y und weist diesen z zu.</p>\n\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> x <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> y <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token number\">20</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> z <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> Math<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">min</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>x<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> y<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>","titleAsText":"Einsatz von Math.min()"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"example_clipping_a_value_with_math.min","title":"Wert mittels&nbsp;<code>Math.min()</code> begrenzen","isH3":true,"content":"<p><code>Math.min()</code>&nbsp;wird oftmals verwendet um einen Wert so zu begrenzen, dass dieser nicht größer als ein gesetztes Limit werden kann. So kann dies</p>\n\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> x <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">f</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>foo<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>x <span class=\"token operator\">&gt;</span> limit<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  x <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> limit<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n\n<p>auch folgendermaßen formuliert werden</p>\n\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> x <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> Math<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">min</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token function\">f</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>foo<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> limit<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n\n<p>Analog kann <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/max\"><code>Math.max()</code></a> verwendet werden um einen Mindestwert zu realisieren.</p>","titleAsText":"Wert mittels Math.min() begrenzen"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"specifications","title":"Spezifikationen","isH3":false,"content":"<table class=\"standard-table\">\n <tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Spezifikation</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Status</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Kommentar</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://www.ecma-international.org/publications/files/ECMA-ST-ARCH/ECMA-262,%201st%20edition,%20June%201997.pdf\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" title=\"Die 'ECMAScript 1st Edition (ECMA-262)' Spezifikation\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript 1st Edition (ECMA-262)</a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-standard\">Standard</span></td>\n   <td>Initiale Definition. Implementiert in JavaScript 1.0.</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://www.ecma-international.org/ecma-262/5.1/#sec-15.8.2.12\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript 5.1 (ECMA-262)<br><small lang=\"de\">Die Definition von 'Math.min' in dieser Spezifikation.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-standard\">Standard</span></td>\n   <td>&nbsp;</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://www.ecma-international.org/ecma-262/6.0/#sec-math.min\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript 2015 (6th Edition, ECMA-262)<br><small lang=\"de\">Die Definition von 'Math.min' in dieser Spezifikation.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-standard\">Standard</span></td>\n   <td>&nbsp;</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-math.min\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript (ECMA-262)<br><small lang=\"de\">Die Definition von 'Math.min' in dieser Spezifikation.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-living\">Lebender Standard</span></td>\n   <td>&nbsp;</td>\n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table>"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browserkompatibilität","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"javascript.builtins.Math.min","dataURL":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/min/bcd.json"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p></p><p></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"Siehe auch","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math/max\"><code>Math.max()</code></a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Beschreibung","id":"description"},{"text":"Beispiele","id":"examples"},{"text":"Spezifikationen","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browserkompatibilität","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"Siehe auch","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"Die Math.min() Funktion gibt den Wert der kleinsten übergebenen Zahl zurück oder NaN, wenn ein Parameter keine Zahl ist und auch nicht in eine Zahl konvertiert werden kann.","popularity":0.0005,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"Math.min()","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)"},{"title":"Math.min()","locale":"es","native":"Español"},{"title":"Math.min()","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"Math.min()","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"Math.min()","locale":"ko","native":"한국어"},{"title":"Math.min()","locale":"pl","native":"Polski"},{"title":"Math.min()","locale":"pt-BR","native":"Português (do Brasil)"},{"title":"Math.min()","locale":"ru","native":"Русский"},{"title":"Math.min()","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"}],"source":{"folder":"de/web/javascript/reference/global_objects/math/min","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/blob/main/files/de/web/javascript/reference/global_objects/math/min/index.html","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/commit/5fe4ab11259b37914fab41914e84897fea47d143","filename":"index.html"},"parents":[{"uri":"/de/docs/Web","title":"Webtechnologien für Entwickler"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript","title":"JavaScript"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference","title":"JavaScript-Referenz"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects","title":"Globale Objekte"},{"uri":"/de/docs